{"UNSCALE":[{"def":"To divest of scales; to remove scales from.","pos":""}],"UNSCAPABLE":[{"def":"Not be escaped; inevitable.","pos":""},{"def":"Having no scepter.","pos":""}],"UNSCIENCE":[{"def":"Want of science or knowledge; ignorance.","pos":""}],"UNSCREW":[{"def":"To draw the screws from; to loose from screws; to loosen or withdraw (anything, as a screw) by turning it.","pos":""}],"UNSCRUPULOUS":[{"def":"Not scrupulous; unprincipled.","pos":""}],"UNSCUTCHEONED":[{"def":"Destitute of an escutcheon.","pos":""}]}